_meanings:
{@--1@} ({%a%}) To remember, bear or keep
in mind, recollect, call to mind,
be aware of; {#smarosa surasanIrAM tatra#} 
{#godAvarIM vA smarasi ca#} 
{#tadupAMtezvAvayorvartanAni#} <ls>U. 1. 26.</ls> ({%b%}) To call to mind,
call upon mentally, think of;  
{#smarAtmano'BIzwadevatAM#} <ls>Pt. 1</ls>; <ls>R. 15. 45</ls>

{@--2@} To recite mentally or call upon
the name of a deity &c.; {#yaH#} 
{#smaretpuMqarIkAkzaM sabAhyAByaMtaraH SuciH#}.

{@--3@} To
lay down or record in a Smṛti;
{#taTA ca smaraMti#}.

{@--5@} To 
remember with regret, yearn after,
long or desire for (<ab>oft.</ab> with <ab>gen.</ab>);
{#smartuM disaMti na divaH surasuMdarIByaH#}  
<ls>Ki. 5. 28</ls>; {#kaccidBartuH smarasi rasike tvaM hi tasya#}
{#priyeti#} <ls>Me. 85</ls>; <ls>Mu. 5. 14</ls>; {#BavatyAH#}
{#smaratAtyarTamarpitaH sAdaraM mama#} <ls>Bk. 8. 118.</ls>

{@--1@} To cause to
remember, remind, put in mind
of, call to mind; {#anena#} 
{#matpriyABiyogena smArayasi me pUrvaSizyAM sOdAminIM#}
<ls>Māl. 1</ls>; sometimes with two <ab>acc.</ab>;
{#api caMdraguptadozA atikrAMtapArTivaguRAn#}
{#smArayaMti prakftIH#} <ls>Mu. 1</ls>; {#ya eva#} 
{#duHsmaraH kAlastameva smAritA vayaM#} <ls>U. 6. 34.</ls>
